# GymBro API — Documentation System

Before any backend task, read the one doc that owns your topic. Start at [`../../README.md`](../../README.md); the
deep docs live in [`../../docs/`](../../docs/). Repo conventions: [`../../CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md).

| What you need | Read |
|---|---|
| Architecture, modules, boundaries, conventions | `../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| Domain entities, EF filters, tenancy, migrations | `../../docs/DATABASE.md` |
| Authorization, roles, permission matrix, tenant isolation | `../../docs/PERMISSIONS.md` |
| Token lifecycle (access/refresh/revocation) | `../../docs/AUTHENTICATION.md` |
| Lifecycle rules (plan/assignment/session/membership) | `../../docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` |
| End-to-end flows (onboarding, invites, sessions) | `../../docs/USER_FLOWS.md` |
| Tests | `../../docs/TESTING.md` |
| Config, migrations, deploy | `../../docs/DEPLOYMENT.md` |

## Key conventions

- All handlers return `Result`/`Result<T>` — never throw for business rules
- Controllers only map `Error.Code` → HTTP status codes (thin controllers)
- EF global filters: tenant isolation + soft-delete (admin bypasses both)
- `X-Tenant-Id` required for tenant-scoped calls; read via `ICurrentUser`/`ITenantContext`, never raw
- FluentValidation validators live beside their command files
- MediatR pipeline (order): `ValidationBehavior` → `AuthorizationBehavior` → `PlatformAdminBehavior`
- Namespaces: `Modules.<Module>Module.<Layer>.<Subfolder>` (folders are `Modules.X`)
- DTO mapping: explicit only in `Application/Mapping/<Module>Mapping.cs`

## Update rules (MANDATORY)

When behavior changes, update the **one** `docs/*` file that owns that fact:

- New/changed endpoint, module dependency, or convention → `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- New entity / field / EF filter → `DATABASE.md`
- Permission or tenant-isolation change → `PERMISSIONS.md`
- Token lifecycle change → `AUTHENTICATION.md`
- Lifecycle rule (plan/assignment/session/membership) → `BUSINESS_RULES.md`
- Flow change (onboarding, invite, session) → `USER_FLOWS.md`

Do not duplicate a fact across docs; link instead.
